member.summary: This enumeration specifies the polarity of the external trigger.

member.name: T:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.MarkerRouting
member.summary: This enumeration specifies the type of marker routing.

member.name: T:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.TriggerType
member.summary: This enumeration specifies the trigger setup mode.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.TriggerType.Single
member.summary: Selects the single mode where the sequence is played once following the selected trigger.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.TriggerType.Gate
member.summary: Selects the gated mode. The sequence plays continuously when the gating signal is inactive. The gating signal is supplied externally via whichever trigger port is selected.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.TriggerType.SegmentAdvance
member.summary: Selects a segment advance mode. In this mode the selected trigger controls the advance to the next segment.

member.name: T:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.TriggerSource
member.summary: This enumeration specifies the trigger source selection.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.TriggerSource.External
member.summary: Trgger by external trigger input signal for trigger.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.TriggerSource.Bus
member.summary: Trigger by GPIB or LAN (*TRG or GET).

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.TriggerSource.TriggerKey
member.summary: Trigger by pressing the front panel Trigger hardkey.

member.name: T:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.ExternalSource
member.summary: This enumeration specifies an external trigger source.

member.name: T:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.Continuous
member.summary: This enumeration specifies the trigger continuous mode.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.Continuous.FreeRun
member.summary: Sets the continuous mode to Free Run. In this mode the sequence plays continously and does not respond to triggers.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.Continuous.TriggerRun
member.summary: Sets the continuous mode to Trigger and Run. In this mode the sequence plays continuously on receipt of the first trigger and does not respond to further triggers.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.Continuous.ResetRun
member.summary: Sets the continuous mode to Reset and Run. In this mode the sequence plays continuously on receipt of the first trigger. On subsequent triggers it resets and runs again.

member.name: T:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SingleTrigger
member.summary: This enumeration specifies the retrigger mode while TriggerType is Single.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SingleTrigger.RestartOnTrigger
member.summary: A trigger received while a sequence is playing out causes an immediate reset and the sequence runs again from the start.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SingleTrigger.NoRetrigger
member.summary: A trigger received while a sequence is playing out is ignored.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SingleTrigger.BufferedTrigger
member.summary: A trigger received while a sequence is playing out causes the sequence to be played a further time after the current sequence is complete.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.ModFilter
member.summary: Gets or sets a filter to the I/Q signal that is modulated onto the RF Signal.
member.remarks:
This parameter is only available for ESG/PSG. Exception will be thrown when it is applied to other instruments.
There is a 40 MHz low pass filter in the I/Q signal path before the IQ modulator. The filter helps reduce broadband noise and spurs for signals with an 80 MHz or less RF bandwidth. This parameter should be set to Through when using external IQ inputs and for signals that have RF bandwidths greater than 80 MHz. These filters have no affect on the PSG Option 015 Wideband signal path. The modulator filter value is used by the correction routine on download.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.IqOutputFilter
member.summary: Gets or sets a filter to the I/Q signal out the rear panel of the instrument.
member.remarks: This parameter is only available for ESG/PSG. Exception will be thrown when it is applied to other instruments.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.IQModulationAttenuationMode
member.summary: Gets or sets the attenuates value selection mode to the I/Q signals being modulated through the RF system.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.IQModulationAttenuation
member.summary: Gets or sets the attenuator value to the I/Q signals being modulated through the RF system.
member.remarks: The Modulator Attenuator is an electronic attenuator in the IQ path before the IQ modulator. The attenuation can be adjusted to optimize signal performance at the RF output. The signal generator will automatically set this value when Modulator Attenuator is set to Auto. When ALC Enable is On, the RF output Amplitude will not change while the attenuator value is changed until the ALC range is exceeded. The modulator attenuator value is used by corrections on download.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.HighCrestEnabled
member.summary: Gets or sets the value indicating whether the High Crest Mode is on or not.
member.remarks:
This parameter is only available for ESG/PSG. Exception will be thrown when it is applied to other instruments.
High Crest Mode changes operating conditions to accommodate I/Q waveforms with high crest factor. The Maximum output level is reduced and power level accuracy is degraded.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.IQSkew
member.summary: Gets or sets the I/Q skew value, which is a time delay between I and Q. A positive value makes I later than Q.
member.remarks: This value affects both the external I/Q output signals and the baseband signal modulated on the RF output. This IqSkewPath must also be specified. Cannot be used with constant envelope modulation, nor can it affect I/Q inputs. The limits are affected by the rate of the current format. Signal degradation can occur for large adjustmanets.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.IqTimingDelay
member.summary: Gets or sets the absolute phase of both I and Q with respect to triggers and markers. A Positive value makes I and Q later.
member.remarks: This value affects on the RF output. This feature is not compatible with constant envelope modulations and signals connected to the external I/Q inputs. The limits are affected by the rate of the current format. Signal degradation can occur for large adjustments.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.CarrierToNoiseRatio
member.summary: Gets or sets the carrier to noise ratio in dB. The carrier power defined as the total modulated signal power before noise is added. The noise power is intergrated over a bandwidth equal to the symbol rate, the chip rate, or in the case of Dual Arb, the specified carrier bandwidth.
member.remarks: Using Realtime noise will require the instrument license.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.CarrierBandwidth
member.summary: Gets or sets the baseband bandwidth over which the noise power is integrated for the Carrier to Noise ratio.
member.remarks:
Cannot be greater than the current sample rate or instrument I/Q bandwidth. The noise will have a flat bandwidth much wider than this value typically.
Using Realtime noise will require the instrument license.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigD.NoiseBandwidthFactor
member.summary: Gets or sets the RF flat noise bandwidth to be either at least 0.8 times the sample rate for a bandwidth factor of 1, or 1.6 times the sample rate if the bandwidth factor is 2.
member.remarks:
This parameter is only available for ESG/PSG. Exception will be thrown when it is applied to other instruments.
When the bandwidth factor is 2 and the sample rate is greater than 50 Msample/sec, noise cannot be enabled. bandwidth be that many times wider than the signal bandwidth.
Some instrument do not have this parameter. Using Realtime noise will require the instrument license.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigM9384B.IQSkew
member.summary: Gets or sets the I/Q skew value, which is a time delay between I and Q. A positive value makes I later than Q.
member.remarks: This value affects both the external I/Q output signals and the baseband signal modulated on the RF output. This IqSkewPath must also be specified. Cannot be used with constant envelope modulation, nor can it affect I/Q inputs. The limits are affected by the rate of the current format. Signal degradation can occur for large adjustmanets.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.SigGenConfigM9384B.IqTimingDelay
member.summary: Gets or sets the absolute phase of both I and Q with respect to triggers and markers. A Positive value makes I and Q later.
member.remarks: This value affects on the RF output. This feature is not compatible with constant envelope modulations and signals connected to the external I/Q inputs. The limits are affected by the rate of the current format. Signal degradation can occur for large adjustments.

member.name: T:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API
member.summary: Represents the base class of and which manage all the functions of WLAN waveform generation and hardware connection.
member.example: See and to get examples of different programming languages.

member.name: M:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.New
member.summary: Creates a new application state file and restores all settings to default values. The hardware settings may not match those currently shown in the application.

member.name: M:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.Generate
member.summary: Generates one waveform or multiple waveforms.

member.name: M:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.Download
member.summary: Downloads the generated waveforms into signal generators.
member.exception: Instrument is not connected.

member.name: M:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.OpenSettingsFile(System.String)
member.summary: Opens a settings file with a specific file name. After a settings file is open, the WaveformSetup, SignalGenerator and all the parameters that belong to them should be retrieved from the API object.
member.param: An absolute path for the settings file.
member.exception: path is a null reference.
The file specified by path is not found.
member.remarks:
WaveformSetup and Hardware settings are updated from the settings file. If the old WaveformSetup or Hardware has been kept in a variable, the variable should be updated. The parameters (such as Carrier, Payload and MacHeader) that belong to them should be updated too. An or will be thrown if these objects are used but haven't been updated after OpenSettingsFile.
The hardware settings may not match those currently shown in the application.

member.name: M:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.SaveSettingsFile(System.String)
member.summary: Saves a settings file with a specified file name.
member.param: An absolute path for the settings file.
member.exception: path is a null reference.
member.remarks: Save the application state to the specified filename, including all hardware parameters and instrument IO configuration.

member.name: M:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.ExportWaveform(System.String[])
member.summary: Exports one waveform or multiple waveforms to the disk.
member.param: The paths of the waveform files to be exported.
member.remarks: The exported waveform can be downloaded via Agilent Signal Studio Toolkit. The exported file name suffix ".wfm" should be added if Toolkit will be used to do the download.
member.exception: paths is a null reference.
The Length of paths doesn't match the number of signal generators.

member.name: M:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.GetCCDFResult(System.Int32,Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.CCDFMode,Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.CCDFResEnum)
member.summary: This method allows you to query a specific CCDF result for 802.11n, 802.11ac and 802.11ah. It should be called after Generate()
member.param: The index of waveform to look at. The waveforms are arranged firstly in order of segments and then in order of transmitter. For example, if there are 2 segments, and each segment has 3 transmitters, then the Indies of waveforms belonging to first segment are 0, 1 and 2 in terms of transmitter Id. While the waveforms of the second segment will be indexed 3, 4 and 5.
Specify the range of waveform over which the statistic of CCDF is taken.
Specify which statics to look at. It would be 10%, 1%, 0.1%, 0.01%, 0.001%, 0.0001%, and Peak.
member.returns: The ccdf of the specified percentage. The unit is dB.

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.CCDFMode.EntireWaveform
member.summary: CCDF is measured over the entire waveform

member.name: F:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.API.CCDFMode.Burst
member.summary: CCDF is measured over the active burst portion without idle interval.

member.name: P:Agilent.SignalStudio.N7617.BeaconFrameConfig.HexByteOrder
member.summary: Gets or sets the bytes' order of a hexadecimal parameter that is input onto GUI. There are two modes, little endian and big endian.
member.remarks: Little endian means the leftmost byte(two digits of hexadecimal value) of input is the one with least significance. Therefore, it will be transmitted first in beacon frame. While big median means the leftmost byte is the most significent one and should be transmitted lastly in a beacon frame. Note: Hex Input Order has no effect on the parameters need to be set in a form other than hexadecimal. Some parameter is a numerical value itself, but it needs to be set in a form of hexadecimal on the GUI. Thus, when set it from the GUI, you have to consider the used endianness, but when you set it with API, you don't have to. Instead, you can directly set its nemeric value.")]
member.example: For examble, a numeric value 3215267533596, whose hexadecimal form is 0x2EC9CE1131C, is required to set on the GUI in a form of hexadecimal. Then in the case of little endian, it should be input onto the GUI as 1C13E19CEC2, while in the case of big endian, it should be 2EC9CE1131C.
